ectrum and quantum numbers of excited states. Moreover, the symmetry\nclass can be partially determined from the quantum numbers of the four\ndegenerate ground states on the torus. We also extend our results to arbitrary\nAbelian topological orders, and compare our classification with the related\nprojective symmetry group classification of parton mean-field theories. Our\nresults provide a framework for understanding and probing the sharp\ndistinctions among symmetric Z2 spin liquids, and are a first step toward a\nfull classification of symmetric topologically ordered phases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Dec 2012 00:39:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 16 Dec 2012 18:04:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 14 Mar 2013 14:41:21 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 8 Apr 2013 22:40:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-04-10"}
