les are sensitive primarily to temporal\nvariations in Sigma and scale variations in mu. We argue that the inclusion of\n21 cm intensity maps will significantly improve constraints on any cosmological\ndeviations from General Relativity in large-scale structure in a very\ncost-effective manner.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Dec 2012 14:10:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Mar 2013 14:13:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-04-26"}
